  "local_port": 60854,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you deposit cash at an ATM?",
  "response": "Depositing cash at an ATM is a straightforward process, but the exact steps can vary slightly depending on the bank and the type of ATM you are using. Here is a general guide to depositing cash at an ATM:\n\n1. **Find an ATM that accepts deposits:** Not all ATMs accept cash deposits, so ensure the ATM you choose can take deposits, preferably one from your bank or credit union to avoid potential fees.\n\n2. **Prepare your cash:** Organize the bills so they are flat and not folded. Remove any paper clips, rubber bands, or envelopes, as they can interfere with the machine.\n\n3. **Insert your ATM or debit card:** Enter the card into the ATM and follow the on-screen prompts. You'll usually be asked to input your Personal Identification Number (PIN).\n\n4. **Select \"Deposit\":** Once logged in, you'll be given several transaction options. Choose \"Deposit\" and then select \"Cash\" as the deposit type.\n\n5. **Insert cash into the ATM:** The machine will indicate where to insert the cash. Some ATMs require you to feed the bills into a slot, while others have deposit envelopes that you fill and insert. If envelopes are used, you may need to select \"Deposit cash with envelope\" or similar.\n\n6. **Confirm the amount:** The ATM will count the cash and display the total amount. Confirm the amount is correct. If the ATM misreads the amount, cancel the transaction or follow the prompts to recount or adjust the total.\n\n7. **Complete the transaction:** Once confirmed, choose whether you want a receipt and finalize the deposit. The ATM will process the transaction and return your card.\n\n8. **Secure your receipt and card:** Make sure to take your card and any receipt or documentation provided. Keep it until you can verify the deposit on your account.\n\nEnsure you're aware of any holds on deposited funds, as policies vary by bank. If you encounter any issues, such as a machine error, contact your bank immediately for assistance.",
